I took the width of the sandwich (wich was three inches) and added it until I got to the width of the box (wich was 18 inches). Finally I used the number of how many times it took me to get to 18 and used that number (wich was 6) to let me know how many sandwitches would fit in the width of the box. Now that I had the number 6 as my width number I had to figure out how many sandwitches would fit in the length of the box. The first thing I had to do was take a quick look at the length of the box. The length of the box was 18 inches. Next I looked at the length of the sandwich. The length of the sandwich was 12 inches.Now I did the same thing as before but only going up to 12. The number I got was 4. Now here is the hardest part. I know six sandwiches will fit in one row and I know there can be 4 rows of sandwiches. So if six sanwiches can fit in each row and we can have four rows of sandwiches we have enough room for 4 rows of six! data_answer: I think 23 sandwiches can fit in the box because first I multiplied the length and the width of the box which are 12 in. and 18 in. to find the area of the box . The area is 116 sq. in. . Next , I multiplied the length and the width of the sandwich which are 3 in. and 3 in. to find the area of the sandwich .The area is 9 sq. in. . Third  , I broke 116 sq. in. into 16 and 100 sq. in. so when I divide 116 sq. in. I won't have that much trouble dividing. Fourth , I divided 16 sq. in. / 9 sq. in. to find one of the partial products of 116 sq. in. / 9 sq. in. and got 1  with  a remainder of  7 . Fith , I divided 100 sq. in. / 9 sq. in. to find one of the partial products of 216 sq. in. / 9 sq. in. . I got 11 with a remainder of 1 .
